502:/*
503:   DRAM_RW is the R/W line to the DRAM memory, and it is a buffered version of the CPU R/W line.  It is held 
504:   in preset by CPU_AS (high means we are not in a bus cycle), CPU_RESET,  and DRAM_REFRESH_RAS.  
505:   The DRAM_REFRESH_RAS makes sure the DRAM_RW line is high (read) during the refresh cycle.  Since it is gated
506:   the DRAM_RW will stay high for about 1/2 clocks after the DRAM_REFRESH_RAS goes high.  That meets the datasheet
