574:   location relative to a normal memory access cycle (DRAM or not).  When both conditions are met 
575:   this state machine will start counting and at specified times trigger the CAS and RAS lines for
576:   a refresh cycle.
577:
578:   REFRESH_COUNTER_RESET is active low, so when it is low we want to assert(high) the reset of the state time flip flops 
